body:
Using `type` with local type parameters or `Self` should have a clearer error.

Reproduce with: [(playpen link)](https://play.rust-lang.org/?gist=a93fa3b44bc0c638b06f3d6975e57c36&version=nightly&backtrace=0)

```rust
struct Foo;

impl Foo {
    fn method<T>(&self) {
        type X = (Self, T);
    }
}
```

Current errors have a suggestion ("try..") that doesn't apply.

```rust
error[E0401]: can't use type parameters from outer function; try using a local type parameter instead
 --> <anon>:6:19
  |
6 |         type X = (Self, T);
  |                   ^^^^ use of type variable from outer function

error[E0401]: can't use type parameters from outer function; try using a local type parameter instead
 --> <anon>:6:25
  |
6 |         type X = (Self, T);
  |                         ^ use of type variable from outer function
```
